@DATABASE "Head Over Heels"
@NODE "MAIN" "SPECCY POKES - H - Head Over Heels"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   ZX SPECTRUM (SPECCY heheh) POKES - H
                   ====================================

                              Head Over Heels
                              ===============


DESCRIPTION              POKE
===========              ====

@{"Immunity      " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(35313,0) ZXAMPoke(35314,62) ZXAMPoke(35315,153)"}          35313,0:35314,62:35315,153
@{"Infinite Lives" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(42198,24)"}          42198,24
@{"Springy Jumps " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(35333,0) ZXAMPoke(35334,0)"}          35333,0:35334,0
@{"Mega Jumps    " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(43132,0)"}          43132,0

                         The Infinite Lives POKE makes your lives loop to 99
                         once you reach 0.

                         OK.. Head Over Heels is one WEIRD game on the emulator.
                         For some BIZARRE reason, if you choose to have sound
                         the game crashes as soon as you switch to HEELS. I have
                         absolutely NO idea why this is, but if you switch the
                         sound off (PARDON on the sound control screen), the
                         game works fine! I don't know if this is only the
                         version I have (from Speccy Sensations 2), but I tried
                         the three different versions on the CD (nice to see
                         no duplication eh? heheh), and it was ALWAYS the
                         same! ARRGGHH!!!!

                         Rastan.
@endnode
